(3164, 'Death 101: Shaping the Future of Global Health', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning.', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning. All features and materials may not be all available. Check back often to see when new course start dates are announced.  Death 101 enables students to investigate health problems affecting large populations â the whole world in fact! By understanding the big numbers in global mortality and their causes and distributions, this course teaches you to think numerically about global health. We use real data from real people to ask the questions: What are the major causes of death in the world? Why do we need cause of death statistics? How does counting the dead help the living? Death 101 is designed for MOOC students and is built for online learning. Â  We begin with an historical perspective on global mortality and end with a hopeful look toward future trends. In between, you will learn about the avoidability of death prior to old age, mortality rates, specific diseases such as HIV, malaria, childhood conditions, chronic diseases, and risk factors such as smoking. Death 101 will help you use population statistics to understand how rapid gains in health are possible. FAQ So, is this going to be morbid or what? Studying death can be a touchy topic, but that doesnât mean it has to be dead boring. We have tried our best to make the course material lively and accessible. Youâve piqued my interest, but the topic sounds scary. Donât let the title scare you! Death 101âs motivation is to analyze information about the global dead in order to help the living.Â  Wait, did you say free? Yes, you can audit this course completely free! The lectures, readings, and assignments are all provided free to students. What a time to be alive! Count me in! What will I need for this course? All course materials are provided online. Some assignments will require a spreadsheet or graphing software and we will provide links to free options should your computer not have one. When can I watch the lectures? New material will be released each week on Monday. Will lectures be captioned with transcripts? Yes, each video will have an English transcript. ', 'https://edx.org/course/death-101-shaping-future-global-health-university-torontox-d101x', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/dCLrwN2gXj0?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 35, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/death-101-shaping-the-future-of-global-health_378x225_n.jpg?itok=qQLRsaI9', 'Biology & Life Sciences', 'edX', 0, 'Introductory', 'no', 'University of TorontoX', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3165, 'Debt Sustainability Analysis', 'What causes a countryâs debt to become unsustainable?', 'What causes a countryâs debt to become unsustainable? How do we assess debt sustainability of public and external debt? How can countries manage their debt portfolio? This online course aims to provide a comprehensive overview of debt sustainability analysis (DSA) and a medium-term debt management strategy framework adopted by the IMF and the World Bank. Specifically, the course will: (i) introduce the main principles of debt sustainability; (ii) cover recently updated DSA frameworks â both for advanced and emerging markets and for low-income countries â with an emphasis on country data; (iii) present a medium-term debt management strategy (MTDS) framework; and (iv) illustrate debt sustainability analysis under uncertainty. Whether you have a professional interest in debt sustainability or debt management or you are simply curious about these issues, we hope that you will join us in this in-depth study of one of the most critical and current issues in economic policy today! Debt Sustainability Analysis is offered by the IMF with financial support from the Government of Belgium. ', 'https://edx.org/course/debt-sustainability-analysis-imfx-dsax', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/iKslqDDdF6U?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-10-07', 42, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/dsa-378x225.jpg?itok=dhhbzSW9', 'Economics & Finance', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'no', 'IMFx', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3166, 'Decision Skills: Power Tools to Build Your Life', 'Have you ever faced a decision you really struggled over, but just couldn''t find your way?', 'Have you ever faced a decision you really struggled over, but just couldn''t find your way? Imagine you had been given a set of tools, so you were confident of making the best choice you could make. This course provides a path to developing those decision skills and improving your life. Good decision-making is an essential life skill most people acquire through trial and error. Few have had the benefit of formal training in decision making or are aware of decision science. This course demonstrates how a framework to help us make better decisions, decision quality, can help overcome common mistakes humans fall into, decision traps. The principles and practice of decision quality have been successfully applied in business, medicine, and engineering. Through our work with teachers, schools, and students, we have witnessed the tremendous value this material brings through helping individuals and groups resolve their toughest dilemmas.', 'https://novoed.com/decision-skills-9', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/pFNsMutC0zs?vq=auto&rel=0&showinfo=0&autohide=1&wmode=transparent&origin=https://novoed.com', '2015-11-09', 39, '', '', 'NovoEd', -1, 'English', 'no', 'Decision Education Foundation', '2015-11-24 23:09:29'),
