(134, 'Corpus Linguistics: Method, Analysis, Interpretation', 'Offers practical introduction to the methodology of corpus linguistics for researchers in social sciences and humanities', 'The course aims to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/corpus-linguistics', '', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/9f/regular_339ff074-1f50-4a77-a9d8-822cf939be13.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:01:56'),
(135, 'The European Discovery of China', 'Explore Chinese history through the eyes of Western travellers, discoverers and missionaries, with this free online course.', 'This free online course focuses on when and how the West first approached China. We will explore the influence that the discovery of China exerted on late medieval and early modern European minds.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/european-discovery-china', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3990564.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/04/regular_7104226d-9edf-44b2-8bb4-956bebc969aa.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Pompeu Fabra University Barcelona', '2015-11-04 00:01:57'),
(136, 'Dyslexia and Foreign Language Teaching', 'Gain practical tools and theoretical insights to help dyslexic students learn second languages, with this free online course.', 'Dyslexia affects 10-15% of the population. Dyslexic students are often either exempted from the study of additional languages or they underperform in foreign language classes.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dyslexia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2555787.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/67/6c/regular_676cb58f-d5b5-4b13-9aa1-7b8bb2477e99.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:01:57'),
(137, 'Muslims in Britain: Changes and Challenges', 'Develop your understanding of Muslims and their faith through an exploration of communities in Britain.', 'Islam is the second largest religion in the world today and dominates much of the current geopolitical discourse. People are increasingly bombarded by dramatic and at times disturbing headlines. Yet general knowledge of Muslims and their faith can be poor. There is consequently a need for a balanced and well-informed understanding of the current debates around this internationally significant topic.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/muslims-in-britain', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2296530.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d8/1a/regular_d81a635c-cda9-41d4-b9aa-8b7d997970dc.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Cardiff University', '2015-11-04 00:01:58'),
(138, 'Professional Practices for English Language Teaching', 'A free online continuing professional development (CPD) course for people who are teaching English as a foreign language.', 'This free online course is for English language teachers around the world. It will help you develop the skills and practices you need for your continuing professional development (CPD).', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/english-language-teaching', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a9/cf/regular_a9cf89ec-1531-4cfe-839c-a23cbabfdea2.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:58'),
(139, 'Understanding IELTS: Techniques for English Language Tests', 'Improve your English and prepare for tests, such as IELTS reading, writing, speaking and listening, with this free online course.', 'Anyone thinking about taking an English language test, such as IELTS, will find this course particularly useful, but all English language learners will benefit from the tips and advice given in the course.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-ielts', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a2/a5/regular_a2a50e02-4364-4ef7-9353-32ce4fda2f09.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:59'),
(140, 'Antiquities Trafficking and Art Crime', 'Delve into the seedy underbelly of the art world, looking at smuggling, theft, fakes, and fraud, with this free online course.', 'The devastation caused by the trafficking of illicit antiquities and the theft of art has gained widespread public attention in recent years.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/art-crime', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5348091.mp4', '2016-02-01', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a0/fd/regular_a0fd2545-9657-4fa4-9769-f4f910c9d9b7.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:02:01'),
(141, 'Crime, Justice and Society', 'Explore the role of the state and criminal justice interventions in producing safe and just societies', 'Crime and criminal justice are vast and fascinating issues that highlight the complexity of defining and solving social problems.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/crime-justice-society', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4928778.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/08/regular_a4085e9b-8156-4c36-b135-378813639661.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:02'),
(142, 'Forensic Psychology: Witness Investigation', 'Discover how psychology can help obtain evidence from eyewitnesses in police investigations and prevent miscarriages of justice.', 'Explore how your own mind works, and discover how the limitations of the human brain can lead to major miscarriages of justice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/forensic-psychology', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2340401.mp4', '2015-09-14', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/bd/09/regular_bd0923f5-3b95-4cf4-b0b9-297a9706d19d.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:03'),
(143, 'Forensic Science and Criminal Justice', 'Learn how police use science in criminal investigations and its role in the criminal justice system with this free online course.', 'Over the past two decades, the criminal justice system has been dramatically affected by technological advances in scientific contributions to the law. The most influential developments have been in the area of DNA profiling, and its forensic applications for both identifying perpetrators and exonerating the innocent.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/forensic-crim-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2493477.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f7/63/regular_f76375a2-d1f5-4625-b706-1b5b5e3a67f9.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leicester', '2015-11-04 00:02:04'),
(144, 'Exploring English: Shakespeare', 'Improve your English language skills by looking at the life and works of William Shakespeare and his enduring popularity.', 'This free online course will look at the life and works of William Shakespeare and take you from his Birthplace in Stratford-upon-Avon to the Globe Theatre in London, from where he secured his central place in English literature.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/explore-english-shakespeare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5517695.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/df/30/regular_df30152c-3fd2-4f96-a151-a39fcead4da3.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:02:05'),
(145, 'Start Writing Fiction', 'This hands-on course helps you to get started with your own fiction writing, focusing on the central skill of creating characters.', 'Start Writing Fiction focuses on a skill which is central to the writing of all stories and novels â creating characters.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/start-writing-fiction', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2648205.mp4', '2016-01-18', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/51/db/regular_51dbd3e2-84fa-4356-ad38-6b76738b6b03.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:06'),
(146, 'An Introduction to Screenwriting', 'This free online course explores the key concepts and fundamental principles involved in the process of screenwriting.', 'Screenplays form the starting point for most dramatic films, the essential work from which all other filmmaking flows. All of the tender romance, terrifying action and memorable lines begin at the screenwriterâs desk. This free online course will introduce you to the basic elements and key concepts behind a professional screenplay.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/screenwriting', '', '2016-02-29', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/70/regular_d270e847-b243-4ba7-ade2-a3b4a551e420.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:06'),
(147, 'World War 1: Changing Faces of Heroism', 'Learn how the war moved us away from traditional views of heroism and created new kinds of heroes and heroines.', 'Did World War 1 make heroism meaningless or was it the conflict that gave it the most meaning? Weâve designed this course in partnership with the BBC to help you explore, discuss and challenge the ways in which World War 1 heroism has been remembered. Our experts will take you through the changing British, French and German views of heroism and discuss important similarities and differences.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-heroism', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3053661.mp4', '2015-10-26', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/40/b5/regular_40b5ca70-dc9c-4f4f-8a13-c75f40ba818d.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:02:07'),
(148, 'Hans Christian Andersenâs Fairy Tales', 'Explore the fairy tale world of HC Andersen - the inspiration behind The Little Mermaid and Frozen - with this free online course.', 'This free online course will introduce you to some of Hans Christian Andersenâs most popular fairy tales, share the story of the writer himself, and discuss his cross-cultural importance today, as the inspiration behind many popular books and movies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/hans-christian-andersens-fairy-tales', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4397780.mp4', '2015-10-19', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/84/b6/regular_84b6a8b0-d253-4b29-982a-97e3f608c85c.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Hans Christian Andersen Centre', '2015-11-04 00:02:07'),
(149, 'Cultural Studies and Modern Languages: an Introduction', 'Explore the culture, language and national identity of eight countries through their books, images, slogans and monuments', 'Are you interested in other countries? Do you want to study and understand other cultures? This free online course will take you on a journey through a number of periods from the medieval to the modern day, from Russia to Europe and all the way to Latin America.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cultural-studies', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428991.mp4', '2015-10-12', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b5/c7/regular_b5c7c300-3189-4c96-ae66-597a6192c138.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bristol', '2015-11-04 00:02:08'),
(150, 'Start Writing Fiction', 'This hands-on course helps you to get started with your own fiction writing, focusing on the central skill of creating characters.', 'Start Writing Fiction focuses on a skill which is central to the writing of all stories and novels â creating characters.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/start-writing-fiction', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2648205.mp4', '2015-10-12', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2c/9b/regular_2c9b9500-3e8d-484c-9285-ada4803496de.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:09'),
(151, 'Shakespeare and his World', 'Together with the Shakespeare Birthplace Trust, Professor Jonathan Bate explores Shakespeare, his works and the world he lived in.', 'William Shakespeare is one of the most famous authors of all time. 2014 marked the 450th anniversary of his birth and his words have inspired and moved people from around the globe for centuries.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shakespeare-and-his-world', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1678642.mp4', '2015-10-05', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1c/c9/regular_1cc90465-ed23-41be-b8f1-12c09e50cc81.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:02:10'),
(152, 'Corpus Linguistics: Method, Analysis, Interpretation', 'Offers practical introduction to the methodology of corpus linguistics for researchers in social sciences and humanities', 'The course aims to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/corpus-linguistics', '', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/9f/regular_339ff074-1f50-4a77-a9d8-822cf939be13.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:10'),
(153, 'How to Read a Mind', 'How do we read and model fictional minds? Introducing cognitive poetics: the application of cognitive science to literary reading.', 'This course offers an introduction to what has come to be known as cognitive poetics. Taking our best current knowledge of how our minds and language work, this course takes you through key questions of literature and reading: why do we feel anything for fictional characters? Why do we get angry, moved, irritated, annoyed or sentimental about imaginary people in imagined worlds? Why do the lives of imaginary minds living in fictional bodies seem to matter so much to readers? The answers to these questions are surprising and empowering.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/how-to-read-a-mind', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/db/regular_46db5b59-369d-4663-a6e6-9f873f6117d1.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:11'),
(154, 'Literature of the English Country House', 'A journey through the literature of English country houses from the time of Thomas More to Oscar Wilde', 'On this free online course, youâll investigate and discuss the role and representation of the English country house in literature, and learn how to build your own authoritative interpretation of these texts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/country-house-literature', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3883219.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2e/f9/regular_2ef9b9c8-0f63-4225-a153-7deabbbcbce8.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:12'),
(155, 'Much Ado about Nothing: in Performance', 'Explore how Much Ado about Nothing is performed and interpreted, from original stagings to the modern day, with this free course.', 'Shakespeareâs much loved play, Much Ado about Nothing, is read and studied all over the world. But it was written to be staged, and can only be fully appreciated and understood through performance.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/much-ado-about-nothing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2369693.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/48/a1/regular_48a12764-dbe4-4337-b76f-7ab4825706fd.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:13'),
(156, 'Reading Macondo: the Works of Gabriel GarcÃ­a MÃ¡rquez', 'Explore why the author of One Hundred Years of Solitude is one of the 20th centuryâs leading writers in this free online course', 'Gabriel GarcÃ­a MÃ¡rquez is a Colombian writer, who won the Literature Nobel Prize in 1982. He has been recognised as one of the worldâs leading writers in the second half of the 20th century.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/macondo-gabriel-garcia-marquez', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3909272.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/98/regular_6998e295-7910-4180-9dfd-4fc18aff0940.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Los Andes', '2015-11-04 00:02:13'),
(157, 'Shakespeares Hamlet: Text, Performance and Culture', 'Experts from the Shakespeare Institute guide an exploration of the most famous play ever staged.', 'Hamlet is the most famous play ever written and the masterpiece of the most important writer in English, William Shakespeare. Its themes of mortality, madness and political succession have given it an enduring fascination - Hamlet has been translated into every major language and adapted for every new medium since it was written.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shakespeares-hamlet', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2196917.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e9/95/regular_e9953aa7-9c18-4279-8e84-6db2d24652e2.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:14'),
(158, 'William Wordsworth: Poetry, People and Place', 'Explore the influence of the Lake District on Wordsworth with this free online course, filmed at his home, Dove Cottage, Grasmere.', 'This free online course will explore the great poetry of William Wordsworth, with an emphasis on his writing process and the inspirational landscape of the Lake District. This course is presented in association with the Wordsworth Trust, Grasmere.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/william-wordsworth', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4010469.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2f/45/regular_2f45d08d-75e4-47c4-ad15-e1ca4329609f.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:14'),
(159, 'Sustainability, Society and You', 'Join us for an introduction to the major global issue of sustainability and discover how you can have a real impact on our future.', 'Sustainability is one of the big global issues of our time. It is crucial that we all play our part in protecting our world for current and future generations. This course provides you with the knowledge and skills to do this by investigating sustainability from multiple angles and exploring what small steps you can take to have a real impact upon all our futures.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-society-and-you', '', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/de/regular_fade2622-3ae1-4ff2-83db-af529fc98553.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:15'),
(160, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Supply Chain Integrity', 'The challenges for food security in tracing and detecting food contamination whether it be by accident or as a result of fraud.', 'Humanity faces a considerable problem in maintaining and enhancing food supplies on a global basis, whilst improving our wellbeing in both the developing and developed world. Obesity and other growing problems related to dietary excess pose huge economic and health implications in the developed world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/global-food-crisis', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1987197.mp4', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/05/regular_09056b37-f7ba-43cb-92ff-bfffcbe948ae.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:16'),
(161, 'Our Changing Climate: Past, Present and Future', 'Find out more about the climate of the past and how climate change can present a number of risks and opportunities.', 'Since early humans first moved out of Africa, the worldâs climate has had a continual impact on our history. Now, the climate itself is being shaped by civilisation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-changing-climate', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5039268.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/36/b7/regular_36b75c03-07cd-4c6f-b0d8-93118da74a70.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:16'),
(162, 'Our Hungry Planet: Agriculture, People and Food Security', 'Consider how the food we grow, buy, eat and throw away relates to the global issue of food security, with this free online course.', 'Food security is a complex, global issue, in which we all play a part. In this free online course, youâll join experts from the School of Agriculture, Policy and Development at the University of Reading, to investigate our relationship with agriculture and your own food habits.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-hungry-planet', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2924674.mp4', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/e6/regular_69e69eca-9803-4fc0-be6c-e1581dce8582.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(163, 'Monitoring Climate from Space', 'Explore our planet from space and learn how Earth observation is used to monitor climate change, with this free online course.', 'It is increasingly essential for us to study climate change across the planet at the highest level of detail possible. But how can we achieve such a comprehensive worldwide view?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-from-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5573782.mp4', '2015-11-30', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/e7/regular_a4e7190e-bd62-49db-a067-c447a53b8709.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'European Space Agency', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(164, 'In the Night Sky: Orion', 'Explore the night sky, discover how stars formed and find out about exoplanets, all through the constellation of Orion.', 'From the basics of astronomy and stargazing, to the science behind the birth of a star, this four week course will change the way you see the night sky. Youâll examine one of the most famous constellations, Orion, who the Ancient Greeks believed was a huntsman placed among the stars by Zeus himself.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/orion', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5334054.mp4', '2016-01-04', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ae/f3/regular_aef30283-74eb-43e5-aac8-b25365494c62.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(165, 'Environmental Humanities: Remaking Nature', 'Learn how the new Environmental Humanities field is shaping how we understand environmental issues, with this free online course.', 'In Environmental Humanities: Remaking Nature, youâll get a broad overview of an emerging area of interdisciplinary research that reframes contemporary environmental challenges using approaches from philosophy, literature, language, history, anthropology, cultural studies and the arts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/remaking-nature', '', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/f0/regular_faf0e28b-3637-46ef-b2db-0b68ff609a67.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:02:18'),
(166, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Sustainable Agrifood Systems', 'This course looks at food insecurity and the challenges to be overcome in order to maintain healthy and sustainable food supplies.', 'This is the second course in a two-part series by Queenâs University Belfast looking at issues concerning the maintenance and enhancement of global food supplies, whilst improving human wellbeing in the developed and developing world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/agrifood', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2089358.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/58/5f/regular_585f12a2-9455-4cf3-b969-3e04243a1934.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:18'),
(167, 'Energy: Thermodynamics in Everyday Life', 'Understand the laws of thermodynamics â and how they govern how we use and lose energy everyday â in this free online course.', 'Energy is essential to life at many levels and its transformation from one form to another â whether in the cells of our bodies or the machines that enable modern society â is governed by the laws of thermodynamics.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5569610.mp4', '2016-02-01', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/62/regular_7162e433-558b-47e2-b263-195f8be0f45b.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'no', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:02:19'),
(168, 'Exploring Possible Futures: Modeling in Environmental and Energy Economics', 'Look to the future, learning how to develop and use models in environmental and energy economics, with this free online course.', 'What will efficient cities look like in future? How do humans contribute to climate change? Is a completely renewable energy supply possible? To explore our possible futures, we need models.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-possible-futures', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4639630.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/db/54/regular_db545c7a-45a5-4b94-af1c-be78e2c85027.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Basel', '2015-11-04 00:02:20'),
(169, 'Moons', 'Explore the many moons of our Solar System. Find out what makes them special. Should we send humans to our Moon again?', 'There are lots of moons in our Solar System. The Earth is the only planet with just a single moon. Some moons are bigger than ours; many are much smaller. There are even tiny moons orbiting some of the asteroids. Some have ongoing volcanic eruptions; others are dead, heavily cratered lumps. One has rivers and lakes of liquid methane. Our own Moon has resources that could help open the Solar System for future exploration. A small handful of moons have conditions below their surfaces where primitive life might exist.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/moons', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2096693.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/58/regular_45589460-fec1-4b42-96d9-ecd89c0a4e13.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:20'),
(170, 'Solving the Energy Puzzle: A Multidisciplinary Approach to Energy Transition', 'Learn how to analyse energy transition cases from technological, legal, economics, spatial, and social perspectives.', 'Since the discovery of fire, mankind has used various energy sources to aid our development. The energy system has been continually changing, as the economy and technology progress.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy-transition', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4509115.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/d2/regular_90d29d5a-20c5-42c7-9b40-229f2233779a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:02:21'),
(171, 'Causes of Climate Change', 'Understand the physical processes behind climate variations in the past, present and future, with this free online course', 'This free online course provides the basis for understanding the underlying physical processes governing climate variations in the past, present and future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-climate-change', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4147256.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a1/84/regular_a184ac4b-f773-4ba7-87bb-fb9a23b1792c.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bergen', '2015-11-04 00:02:22'),
(172, 'Climate Change: Challenges and Solutions', 'This course aims to explain the science of climate change, the risks it poses and the solutions available to reduce those risks.', 'The course is aimed at the level of students entering university, and seeks to provide an inter-disciplinary introduction to what is a broad field. It engages a number of experts from the University of Exeter and a number of partner organisations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-change-challenges-and-solutions', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2136990.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/cb/71/regular_cb71114d-b163-4486-908d-20dadfde623e.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Exeter', '2015-11-04 00:02:23'),
(173, 'Elements of Renewable Energy', 'Learn how sustainable energy from the Greek elements â Earth, Air, Fire and Water â can replace fossil fuels and nuclear power.', 'In recent decades thereâs been increasing global concern about the sustainability of our use of fossil fuels and nuclear power, which has led to increased interest in more sustainable renewable energy sources.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/elements-renewable-energies', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0e/e1/regular_0ee1deec-38ac-46df-82a5-4d4b0f0bad4c.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:23'),
(174, 'Environmental Justice', 'Understand how environmental change affects people, and how we can work together for justice in environmental management.', 'The world faces challenging environmental problems. They are challenging because different people typically contribute differently to environmental change, and because its effects will be felt differently by different people in different places.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/environmental-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428282.mp4', '0000-00-00', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b2/83/regular_b283c88b-3644-499d-b965-cef376be50cd.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:24'),
(175, 'Exploring Our Oceans', 'Explore the half of our world covered by deep ocean, and how our lives affect the hidden face of our planet.', 'The first astronauts to leave the Earthâs orbit saw our âblue planetâ for the first time. But what lies in the half of our world covered by water more than two miles deep? How are our everyday lives connected to the ocean depths, and what challenges and opportunities does this previously hidden realm hold for our future?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-our-oceans', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/e6/regular_d9e61125-ca2d-4240-abba-751ca981345f.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:25'),
(176, 'Fairness and Nature: When Worlds Collide', 'Making decisions about managing natural resources can be difficult; this course explores why fairness needs to be part of policy.', 'This course is about making difficult decisions on the management of natural resources. Different people place different values on nature. For example, some see it as something we should conserve for future generations, others as a resource of financial value to be exploited. Policies about managing nature should be economically and environmentally sound, but they also need to be formulated with social fairness if they are to be sustainable. Inevitably, when there are so many different values, conflicts occur and worlds collide.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/fairness-and-nature', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1345241.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/7b/ee/regular_7beee768-9454-46b4-b4c7-9ec567b8165d.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:02:25'),
(177, 'Global Food Security: Addressing the Challenge', 'How will we feed an extra two billion people by the middle of this century?', 'In this course, we introduce the issue of food security and explore some of the different ways in which it has been described both in research and in practice and consider key concerns for the future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2550056.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/74/1a/regular_741a7f06-e579-4f08-8bc0-a2efb60c4a7a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:26'),
(178, 'Introduction to Ecosystems', 'Gain an understanding of the natural world, how the web of life works, with illustrations from around the world.', 'If we donât grasp why ecosystems function, it becomes harder to determine possible reasons for when they donât, and makes it difficult to identify possible environmental threats to humans. In this course you will discover how organisms are linked together by complex interrelationships, how such links are studied and how the physical properties of a particular habitat interact with the organisms that inhabit it. Using case studies, you will come to learn how knowledge of ecosystems leads to understanding of their individual importance, and how they can be preserved.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ecosystems', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2389989.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/2e/regular_ef2e01b3-f7a4-4358-8d81-53bbf347063a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:27'),
(179, 'Make an Impact: Sustainability for Professionals', 'Find out how to integrate a sustainable development strategy into your company with this free online course', 'This free online course will cover the basic definitions and history of sustainable development and sustainability in business - from a niche interest to the present day.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-for-professionals', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1413352.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/31/d5/regular_31d5e65d-bb75-4eb9-978b-7f882a80e862.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:02:27'),
(180, 'Shale Gas and Fracking: the Politics and Science', 'Hear from all sides of the fracking debate with this free online course. Understand what shale gas is and why it divides opinion.', 'Shale gas is seen by many as a cheap, clean and plentiful source of energy; a low-carbon âgame changerâ helping us meet the worldâs rapidly growing demands for energy and offering greater energy security. Its rapid rise has not been without controversy, however. Earth tremors, surface and groundwater contamination, and the effects of fracking on human and animal health are all high profile concerns.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shale-gas', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2317839.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/3c/ac/regular_3caca682-b4ac-4240-8621-d58a9c0ac586.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:28'),
(181, 'Shipwrecks and Submerged Worlds: Maritime Archaeology', 'Learn how maritime archaeology investigates our changing relationship with the oceans and seas, from 2.5m years ago until today', 'People have explored and depended on the oceans of our planet for millennia. During that time the geography of our world has changed radically as coastal regions have flooded and islands have risen up, or been lost beneath the waves. With 70% of the worldâs surface covered by water, an unparalleled, yet largely untouched record of human life has been left beneath the sea for us to discover, from our earliest ancestors right through to present day. Over the length of this Shipwrecks and Submerged Worlds course we will learn about maritime archaeology together - exploring underwater landscapes from the ancient Mediterranean to the prehistoric North Sea, and consider Shipwrecks from the Indian Ocean to the Pacific coast of the Americas.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shipwrecks', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3259029.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/87/fc/regular_87fc6f31-2a02-4a14-974f-df1d9f62e701.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:28'),
(182, 'Soils: Introducing the World Beneath Our Feet', 'Learn about soils, the variety of life they contain and how humans impact this fragile system, with this free online course.', 'Soils are a vital part of our planetâs functioning, but all too often we take soils for granted. In this free online course, we introduce you to soils and explore the world beneath our feet.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/soils', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3693052.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/e6/regular_42e6e9b4-5a4f-43b4-bd68-ecd46f957777.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:29'),
(183, 'The Science of Nuclear Energy', 'Discover the science behind nuclear energy and its role in energy provision in the past, present and future.', 'With the need to reduce carbon emissions around the world, the way we generate our power has to change and nuclear energy is back on the political agenda. But do you know your fission from your fusion? Would you like the knowledge to make an informed decision?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nuclear-energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3933347.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2c/51/regular_2c51f90d-2504-47bb-8816-c834b4e29b99.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:30'),
(184, 'Water for Liveable and Resilient Cities', 'Learn how water can be used in the planning of cities to improve liveability in the face of climate change and population growth.', 'Water plays a central role in almost every aspect of our urban environment and quality of life in our cities. Alarmingly, the combined impacts of rapid population growth and climate change are now posing a severe threat to the liveability and resilience of our cities.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/liveable-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2131245.mp4', '0000-00-00', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/5a/c0/regular_5ac04df6-27c0-4468-b0d1-96d57f11a7f1.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:02:30'),
(185, 'What Works: Promising Practices in International Development', 'Explore promising strategies in international aid related to agriculture, public health, governance, and poverty reduction.', 'The history of international development is a complicated mixture of hopeful altruism and difficult reality. The media often paint development aid as wasteful spending, leaving the public wondering if any intervention can ever work. Yet can the case be made for a more optimistic outlook on international development?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-works', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2402606.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/fc/regular_17fc7ab1-9d5f-4463-be05-efedf4120f31.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Oslo', '2015-11-04 00:02:31'),
(186, 'The Internet of Things', 'Learn how IoT works, and how to create a successful product or company using it, with this free online course.', 'Entrepreneurs love it, large corporations love it, universities and now even governments love it â welcome to the exciting and emerging world of the Internet of Things (IoT).', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/internet-of-things', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4611259.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8e/44/regular_8e442a5c-4cee-4fd3-8f8f-ed04df2789cd.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:02:34'),
(187, 'Bioprinting: 3D Printing Body Parts', 'Discover how biomaterials and 3D printing collide, to create revolutionary, bioprinted body parts, with this free online course.', 'You may be aware of 3D printing or have seen low-cost 3D printers, which can create plastic toys, replicas and objects of your own design. But did you know that 3D printing is also enabling life-saving and transforming medical procedures, which were unthinkable a few years ago?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/bioprinting', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4894894.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e6/3f/regular_e63f6908-c6bc-4bc2-9059-d18064cac286.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Australian Institute for Innovative Materials, University of Wollongong ', '2015-11-04 00:02:34'),
(188, 'Web Science: How the Web Is Changing the World', 'Explore how the web has changed our world and what the future might hold, with this free online course introducing Web Science.', 'You may already be an avid user of the Web, but this introduction to Web Science will help you better understand it as both a social and technical system - a global information infrastructure, built from the interactions of people and technologies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/web-science', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5294960.mp4', '2015-11-30', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/91/42/regular_914240b3-f131-47cb-90a5-be0a430aa70e.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:35'),
(189, 'Social Media in Healthcare: Opportunities and Challenges', 'Understand how social media is used in healthcare, to improve communication and information sharing, with this free online course.', 'Social media has emerged as a new channel for both seeking information, and for creating and exchanging user-generated content among peers.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/social-media-in-healthcare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5435393.mp4', '2015-11-30', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e4/96/regular_e4961de7-feb1-455e-8114-c9471a3027f9.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Taipei Medical University', '2015-11-04 00:02:36'),
(190, 'Introduction to Cyber Security', 'Our lives depend on online services. Gain essential cyber security knowledge and skills, to help protect your digital life.', 'We shop online. We work online. We play online. We live online. As our lives increasingly depend on digital services, the need to protect our information from being maliciously disrupted or misused is really important.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-cyber-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3488942.mp4', '2016-01-04', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e0/bc/regular_e0bc186c-7d75-445e-acce-21656f172c47.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:37'),
(191, 'Get Started with Online Learning', 'This free online course will explain how you can study online without putting the rest of your life on hold.', 'The internet is playing a bigger role in our lives, as we buy our groceries, manage our finances, share social experiences and otherwise live our lives online. But how many of us have considered studying online?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/online-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4763094.mp4', '2016-01-04', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ce/19/regular_ce19db60-1224-442e-9df3-e38913259994.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:38'),
(192, 'Transmedia Storytelling', 'Learn how to tell compelling stories across multiple platforms, like books, films, games and TV, with this free online course.', 'Stories are increasingly told across a variety of formats, such as books, comics, events, films, games and TV programmes - a trend known as transmedia storytelling or multiplatform storytelling.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/transmedia-storytelling', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5451882.mp4', '2016-01-18', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/40/a7/regular_40a7200a-b643-4bea-b7e4-5e670de9533c.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Sungkyunkwan University (SKKU) ', '2015-11-04 00:02:38'),
(193, 'Digital Leadership: Creating Value Through Technology', 'Digital technologies are changing extraordinarily quickly. This four-week course will introduce you to the new digital landscape.', 'In this course you will learn how to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-leadership', '', '2016-02-08', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b8/88/regular_b888ab0c-c46e-4a35-afa8-9b946a74cfa0.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:39'),
(194, 'Learn to Code for Data Analysis', 'Software and data make the world go round. Learn programming, to analyse and visualise open data, with this free online course.', 'This hands-on course will teach you how to write your own computer programs, one line of code at a time. Youâll learn how to access open data, clean it and analyse it and to produce visualisations. You will also learn how to write up and share your analyses, privately or publicly.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/learn-to-code', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4731244.mp4', '2015-10-26', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1d/79/regular_1d7976bd-1f5e-4c90-a72a-233fe6ce7b49.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:40'),
(195, 'Digital Marketing: Challenges and Insights', 'Explore the latest trends in digital marketing. Get beneath the hype. What are the implications? How will you respond?', 'This short course introduces you to exciting new concepts and applications of digital marketing. It takes an informal âstory tellingâ approach, encouraging you to share your own stories as consumers and/or marketers for the benefit of the learner group as a whole.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-marketing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1756128.mp4', '2015-10-19', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/75/regular_d27599ca-eb59-4fe1-a538-0b1ceffd3e10.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:40'),
(196, 'Begin Programming: Build Your First Mobile Game', 'Learn basic Java programming by developing a simple mobile game that you can run on your computer, Android phone, or tablet.', 'Programming is everywhere: in dishwashers, cars and even space shuttles. This course will help you to understand how programs work and guide you through creating your own computer program â a mobile game.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-programming', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4251365.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c9/9c/regular_c99cbca8-6bf5-44f2-9bb9-17c21efc8e72.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:41'),
(197, 'Introduction to Cyber Security', 'Our lives depend on online services. Gain essential cyber security knowledge and skills, to help protect your digital life.', 'We shop online. We work online. We play online. We live online. As our lives increasingly depend on digital services, the need to protect our information from being maliciously disrupted or misused is really important.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-cyber-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3488942.mp4', '2015-10-05', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/af/ef/regular_afef979f-493c-461a-bfd9-97d30d3cb1eb.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:41'),
(198, 'Begin Robotics', 'Explore the history, anatomy and intelligence of robots with this free online course. Test drive robots using exciting simulations', 'Robots today are roving Mars, collecting data in dangerous environments, hoovering our floors, lifting patients in hospital, building cars and entertaining us in films. And, if you share Bill Gates and Stephen Hawkingâs world view, the super intelligent ones may one day bring about the end of the human race.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-robotics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3697356.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/ce/regular_82ce6165-30a4-440e-ad57-a7e8f9e77220.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:42'),
(199, 'Big Data: Measuring and Predicting Human Behaviour', 'Join us to explore how the vast amounts of data generated today can help us understand and even predict how humans behave.', 'We increasingly rely on networked computer systems and smart cards to support our everyday activities, and everything we do generates data â whether buying bread at the supermarket, taking a ride on public transport, or calling a friend for a chat.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/big-data', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2705064.mp4', '0000-00-00', 9, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a7/57/regular_a7574c1e-db70-49e1-9060-9ba19d00f6f2.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:02:43');
INSERT INTO `course_data` (`id`, `title`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `course_link`, `video_link`, `start_date`, `course_length`, `course_image`, `category`, `site`, `course_fee`, `language`, `certificate`, `university`, `time_scraped`) VALUES
(200, 'Childhood in the Digital Age', 'Delve into the lives of children and discuss the potential benefits and limitations of technology in their lives.', 'Are you a technology optimist or a technology pessimist?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/childhood-in-the-digital-age', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4530272.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/14/f8/regular_14f8f7d0-c6ec-4d94-a99c-acff489aeb38.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:44'),
(201, 'Community Journalism: Digital and Social Media', 'Gain practical skills and insights into hyperlocal journalism, and use digital and social media to create your own news website.', 'Community journalism is a growing area of interest for professional journalists, academics and the wider public. The decline of local newspapers and radio stations, coupled with the low cost of publishing online, means there are more community journalism and hyperlocal websites being launched everyday.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/community-journalism', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2358128.mp4', '0000-00-00', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d3/54/regular_d3548457-a375-456b-8ecc-7533e9050fca.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Cardiff University', '2015-11-04 00:02:46'),
(202, 'Creative Coding', 'Use computer programming as a creative discipline to generate sounds, images, animations and more, with this free online course.', 'Learning to program is no longer just for computer specialists and software developers. People from many different backgrounds now want to understand the basics of programming, because itâs both fun and an increasingly valuable skill.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/creative-coding', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1569932.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8e/98/regular_8e98b3b7-689e-457a-95ac-c1523d7d5242.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:02:47'),
(203, 'Digital Storytelling: Filmmaking for the Web', 'Combine theory and practice to tell powerful stories through film online. Unleash your potential in this free online course.', 'The University of Birmingham, the BBC Academy and Creative Skillset have combined forces, to create this four-week, free online course.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-storytelling', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4315019.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9a/b5/regular_9ab51686-7c98-4e16-ba4b-d59af4d71ce1.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:48'),
(204, 'Teaching Computing', 'A free online course for primary and secondary school teachers who are tackling the Computing curriculum in England.', 'This free online course aims to help teachers in primary schools and at Key Stage 3, who are delivering the Computing curriculum, which was introduced to schools in England in September 2014.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/teaching-computing', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/c5/regular_d2c51ff2-0c67-41aa-ab9c-10e9c1835f4e.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:49'),
(205, 'Sustainability, Society and You', 'Join us for an introduction to the major global issue of sustainability and discover how you can have a real impact on our future.', 'Sustainability is one of the big global issues of our time. It is crucial that we all play our part in protecting our world for current and future generations. This course provides you with the knowledge and skills to do this by investigating sustainability from multiple angles and exploring what small steps you can take to have a real impact upon all our futures.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-society-and-you', '', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/de/regular_fade2622-3ae1-4ff2-83db-af529fc98553.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:50'),
(206, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Supply Chain Integrity', 'The challenges for food security in tracing and detecting food contamination whether it be by accident or as a result of fraud.', 'Humanity faces a considerable problem in maintaining and enhancing food supplies on a global basis, whilst improving our wellbeing in both the developing and developed world. Obesity and other growing problems related to dietary excess pose huge economic and health implications in the developed world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/global-food-crisis', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1987197.mp4', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/05/regular_09056b37-f7ba-43cb-92ff-bfffcbe948ae.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:51'),
(207, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Sustainable Agrifood Systems', 'This course looks at food insecurity and the challenges to be overcome in order to maintain healthy and sustainable food supplies.', 'This is the second course in a two-part series by Queenâs University Belfast looking at issues concerning the maintenance and enhancement of global food supplies, whilst improving human wellbeing in the developed and developing world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/agrifood', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2089358.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/58/5f/regular_585f12a2-9455-4cf3-b969-3e04243a1934.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:52'),
(208, 'Africa: Sustainable Development for All?', 'Learn what progress Africa has made towards inclusive development and consider challenges post-2015 in this free online course.', 'Africa as a continent is rich in natural resources and minerals and has increasing rates of wealth in some countries. The course will explore why there continues to be many sub-Saharan African countries which perform poorly on development indicators for reducing poverty, hunger and unemployment and improving maternal health and access to quality reproductive health services.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/africa-sustainable-development', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3920380.mp4', '2016-01-25', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/32/6a/regular_326a81ea-0cc3-4bde-9ddf-a78ccbeea382.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Aberdeen', '2015-11-04 00:02:52'),
(209, 'Understanding Public Financial Management: How Is Your Money Spent?', 'How do governments acquire and spend public money? Take a fresh look at public financial management with this free online course.', 'What went wrong in Greeceâs handling of its public debt? How does a city government like Detroit go from prosperity to bankruptcy? And how could the looting, theft and corruption in Malawiâs âcashgateâ have been avoided?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/public-financial-management', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5441427.mp4', '2016-01-25', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/12/regular_ef1250d1-3017-48da-b50d-d032a15e5029.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'SOAS, University of London', '2015-11-04 00:02:53'),
(210, 'Military Ethics: An Introduction', 'We explore the ethical responsibilities that weigh on military professionals, who are âmanagers of violenceâ.', 'Military professionals are unusual in having the use of lethal force as a central, defining feature of their role, and unique in the level of force that they are authorized to use. This fact places a considerable ethical weight on military practitioners as well as the civilian decision-makers who authorize military missions.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/military-ethics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5387660.mp4', '2016-02-29', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f2/02/regular_f2020743-f023-4d3a-bac1-fafa5907d58f.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:02:53'),
(211, 'Scotland and Wales Vote 2016: Understanding the Devolved Elections', 'This course wil examine the issues, ideas and institutions involved in the Scottish Parliament and Welsh Assembly elections.', '2016 is an exciting year for elections in the United Kingdom. Towards the end of the year we might have a referendum on the UKâs EU membership, but we definitely know that there will be elections to the Scottish Parliament and Welsh Assembly in May. Both of these institutions have a significant impact on peopleâs lives in Scotland and Wales: they control big public policy issues like health, education and transport.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/scottish-welsh-elections16', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5435747.mp4', '2016-04-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b5/25/regular_b525867d-1a7e-4f70-bda6-760e3fc5a516.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Edinburgh', '2015-11-04 00:02:54'),
(212, 'Crime, Justice and Society', 'Explore the role of the state and criminal justice interventions in producing safe and just societies', 'Crime and criminal justice are vast and fascinating issues that highlight the complexity of defining and solving social problems.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/crime-justice-society', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4928778.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/08/regular_a4085e9b-8156-4c36-b135-378813639661.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:55'),
(213, 'Religion and Conflict', 'Understand and analyze the role of religion in conflicts and peacebuilding in present-day societies, with this free online course.', 'Many conflicts in the world today are framed in terms of religion, but there is much discussion and confusion concerning the precise role religion plays in these conflicts. According to some, conflict and violence are inherent to religion. Others claim that religion is only the guise under which social, economic or political conflicts are fought out. The first step to solving religiously framed conflicts is understanding the role of religion in them, and that is what this free online course is about.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/religion-and-conflict', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3022180.mp4', '2015-10-05', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d7/ef/regular_d7ef63d4-5ee9-409f-9b5f-be27016bc9eb.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:02:56'),
(214, 'Causes of War', 'What causes armed conflict in the world today? Examine current thinking on this critical question with this free online course.', 'This free online course will introduce you to current thinking on the causes of armed conflict in the world today. It looks at a range of modern and historical conflicts and draws on a variety of theories and approaches. It will appeal to anyone with an interest in world affairs.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-war', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2641095.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a0/69/regular_a069122d-914e-4328-8fcd-704562070123.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:02:56'),
(215, 'Challenging Wealth and Income Inequality', 'Explore the concerns about rising generational and economic inequality in developed countries, with this free online course.', 'From religious leaders to heads of state, everyone is talking about economic inequality. What form can such inequality take in different countries? What impact does it have on society? And why should it matter to you?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/inequalities-in-personal-finance', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2763907.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c6/8f/regular_c68fc17f-f2b2-4b0d-b9d3-2ef55bb681d9.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:57'),
(216, 'Cooperation in the Contemporary World: Unlocking International Politics', 'Why do we cooperate? How can we achieve more lasting cooperation? This course explores the puzzle in international politics today.', 'As world leaders seek to find a solution to crises in Syria and Ukraine; economists try to reinvigorate stalling global financial markets; and a range of actors gather to find a consensus on climate change, there has never been a better time to understand the puzzle of cooperation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cooperation-in-the-contemporary-world', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4149980.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1c/c6/regular_1cc604f0-636e-425d-80a9-34ae7880a164.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:58'),
(217, 'Environmental Justice', 'Understand how environmental change affects people, and how we can work together for justice in environmental management.', 'The world faces challenging environmental problems. They are challenging because different people typically contribute differently to environmental change, and because its effects will be felt differently by different people in different places.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/environmental-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428282.mp4', '0000-00-00', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b2/83/regular_b283c88b-3644-499d-b965-cef376be50cd.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:58'),
(218, 'From State Control to Remote Control: Warfare in the 21st Century', 'Explore the impact and ethics of using drones, special ops units and private security firms, with this free online course.', 'States are increasingly using remote control methods, such as drones, private military companies and special operations units, to engage in activities that were traditionally performed by their conventional armed forces.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/remote-control-warfare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2662019.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d8/17/regular_d817f134-8706-4769-a704-12400797fbfc.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:02:59'),
(219, 'Global Food Security: Addressing the Challenge', 'How will we feed an extra two billion people by the middle of this century?', 'In this course, we introduce the issue of food security and explore some of the different ways in which it has been described both in research and in practice and consider key concerns for the future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2550056.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/74/1a/regular_741a7f06-e579-4f08-8bc0-a2efb60c4a7a.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:03:00'),
(220, 'Identity, Conflict and Public Space', 'Explore how people use public spaces around the world to protest and express their identity, with this free online course.', 'In ethnic and political conflicts around the world, public spaces are used by diverse groups of people, to express their identity and protest about their beliefs:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/identity-conflict-and-public-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1401981.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/14/19/regular_141937f4-9e01-430f-b96d-d16c9868e28c.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:03:00'),
(221, 'Lips and Teeth: Korea and China in Modern Times', 'Explore the historical evolution of China and the Korean Peninsula and discover the implications for today.', 'As countries across Asia - and the globe - wrestle with the impact of Chinaâs rise, nowhere are the opportunities and threats of a wealthy and powerful China felt more keenly than next door, on the Korean Peninsula.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/korea-and-china', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2419110.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/60/5e/regular_605e0239-009a-451d-aa14-57eee58b3259.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Yonsei University', '2015-11-04 00:03:01'),
(222, 'Modern Korean History: Liberation, War and Nuclear Ambitions', 'Explore the unique and untold history of North and South Korea - from 1945 to the present - with this free online course.', 'The contemporary history of the Korean peninsula has been a tumultuous tale of decolonization, war and rapid economic development. Both North and South Korea has had an immense impact on the world stage and today many wonder why this region of East Asia appears so frequently in the international news.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/modern-korean-history', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2372067.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ff/51/regular_ff5143af-a195-45ae-9e42-aff3857da80e.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Yonsei University', '2015-11-04 00:03:02'),
(223, 'Propaganda and Ideology in Everyday Life', 'Find out how propaganda is used to instil political ideologies and its impact on our daily lives, with this free online course.', 'This free online course explores the building blocks of our political views: freedom, community, place, justice and choice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/propaganda', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2801553.mp4', '0000-00-00', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/23/regular_ef2351cc-cde8-4ed0-9801-4bfc380e0930.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:03'),
(224, 'Shale Gas and Fracking: the Politics and Science', 'Hear from all sides of the fracking debate with this free online course. Understand what shale gas is and why it divides opinion.', 'Shale gas is seen by many as a cheap, clean and plentiful source of energy; a low-carbon âgame changerâ helping us meet the worldâs rapidly growing demands for energy and offering greater energy security. Its rapid rise has not been without controversy, however. Earth tremors, surface and groundwater contamination, and the effects of fracking on human and animal health are all high profile concerns.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shale-gas', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2317839.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/3c/ac/regular_3caca682-b4ac-4240-8621-d58a9c0ac586.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:03'),
(225, 'Superpowers of the Ancient World: the Near East', 'Experience the worldâs first international age, 3,500 years ago in the ancient Near East, with this free online course.', 'Over four weeks, this free online course explores four ancient Near-Eastern cultures and how they interacted with each other 3,500 years ago.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/superpowers-near-east', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4115194.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/8c/regular_338c724e-a5c0-4318-a826-0d253678383d.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:03:04'),
(226, 'The Lottery of Birth', 'Birth is a lottery. Where, when and to whom you are born and the society into which you are born will influence your life chances.', 'This free online course will look at both the big picture of the âlottery of birthâ and the smaller, human stories. You will examine the inequalities of birth, particularly being born rich or poor and being born female or male.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/lottery-of-birth', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/04/33/regular_04332853-0e02-4bcb-ba23-c4a2275ac789.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:05'),
(227, 'What Works: Promising Practices in International Development', 'Explore promising strategies in international aid related to agriculture, public health, governance, and poverty reduction.', 'The history of international development is a complicated mixture of hopeful altruism and difficult reality. The media often paint development aid as wasteful spending, leaving the public wondering if any intervention can ever work. Yet can the case be made for a more optimistic outlook on international development?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-works', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2402606.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/fc/regular_17fc7ab1-9d5f-4463-be05-efedf4120f31.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Oslo', '2015-11-04 00:03:05'),
(228, 'World War 1: Paris 1919 - A New World Order?', 'This course reassesses the legacy of the Paris Peace Conference (1919) and how it sought to create a new world order.', 'The Paris Peace Conference of 1919 ended a Great War, but it also designed the post-war future. In 1919, world leaders assembled in Paris redrew the map of the world, partitioned and created countries, and ushered in a new era of international relations. The naivety of the peace-makers of 1919 has been justly criticised. However, in setting up a permanent âworld organisationâ, the League of Nations, they changed the management of world affairs forever.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-new-world-order', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2196589.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/23/7e/regular_237e6c99-3f52-4853-96e0-bafa0e3dfdd1.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:03:05'),
(229, 'Improving Your Image: Dental Photography in Practice', 'Learn how to achieve consistent and excellent results in all aspects of dental photography with this free online course.', 'This free course will cover all aspects of the use of digital photography in dental practice: intra-oral, extra-oral, and portraits. Participants will be taken through photography, from the basics of choosing correct equipment and setting it up, to optimum settings, techniques for consistent imaging and the safe storage of images.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dental-photography-in-practice', '', '2015-11-02', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ab/4f/regular_ab4fe1b5-2203-48de-85fa-ad0b5275d473.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:07'),
(230, 'Cracking Mechanics: Further Maths for Engineers', 'Practise the maths, learn the physics, and find out how engineers use both to solve real world problems.', 'The aim of this free online course is to introduce you to some of the physics and maths that engineers find useful. The content comprises: parts of A-level maths and further maths (mechanics); the physical laws which this maths is used to model; and examples of how these skills are employed in mechanical, aerospace, civil, environmental, materials and electrical engineering.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cracking-mechanics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3042441.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/40/regular_454057f3-177d-40d1-a5e3-e549dda27a18.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bristol', '2015-11-04 00:03:08'),
(231, 'Why Do We Age? The Molecular Mechanisms of Ageing', 'Why do we age? Is there a limit to human lifespan? Can we prolong our lives? Find out with this free online course.', 'The âwhyâ and âhowâ of ageing has puzzled mankind ever since it questioned its place in the universe. However, it was only after infectious diseases became more controlled and reliable food supplies became generally available, that the rapid increase of the average lifespan made science turn its attention to study longevity and ageing.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ageing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3155756.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/2a/regular_422a2468-5da5-4fe4-85d9-bd78671b980c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:03:10'),
(232, 'Improving Healthcare Through Clinical Research', 'Find out how medical treatments are discovered, tested and evaluated, to improve healthcare for all, on this free online course.', 'Everything we do in healthcare - every tablet thatâs prescribed, every treatment thatâs given and every test thatâs performed - has to be first discovered and then thoroughly evaluated before it can be put into practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/clinical-research', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5394540.mp4', '2015-11-02', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a8/e8/regular_a8e878c7-6b58-4e07-9895-ae0403ee7540.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:11'),
(233, 'Electrify: An Introduction to Electrical and Electronic Engineering', 'How do we move things with electricity? How do the parts inside your computer work? Find out in Electrify.', 'Engineering is all about using science to make the world a better place and touches our everyday lives; the device youâre reading this on wouldnât exist if it wasnât for electrical and electronic engineers!', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/electrify', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1613333.mp4', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/8d/regular_828d95f9-e363-408a-a9b8-b14f48464d8e.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:03:12'),
(234, 'Our Changing Climate: Past, Present and Future', 'Find out more about the climate of the past and how climate change can present a number of risks and opportunities.', 'Since early humans first moved out of Africa, the worldâs climate has had a continual impact on our history. Now, the climate itself is being shaped by civilisation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-changing-climate', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5039268.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/36/b7/regular_36b75c03-07cd-4c6f-b0d8-93118da74a70.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:03:14'),
(235, 'Real World Calculus: How Maths Drives Formula One and Launches Angry Birds', 'Understand how maths, such as differentiation and integration, is applied in everyday life with this free online calculus course.', 'Mathematics is at the heart of many aspects of modern life. Whether playing a game on your mobile phone, watching a Grand Prix or waking up to sunlight in the morning, maths (and more precisely, calculus) is behind the scenes.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/real-world-calculus', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2633166.mp4', '2015-11-09', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fe/04/regular_fe0442a4-9383-490b-9628-e407def4708c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leicester', '2015-11-04 00:03:15'),
(236, 'Basic Science: Understanding Numbers', 'This course explains how you can use numbers to describe the natural world and make sense of everything from atoms to oceans.', 'This practical, hands-on course will help you to start thinking like a scientist, by using numbers to describe and understand the natural world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-numbers', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3030512.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c2/57/regular_c2574880-125e-464d-a23c-ee56d772dc9c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:16'),
(237, 'Web Science: How the Web Is Changing the World', 'Explore how the web has changed our world and what the future might hold, with this free online course introducing Web Science.', 'You may already be an avid user of the Web, but this introduction to Web Science will help you better understand it as both a social and technical system - a global information infrastructure, built from the interactions of people and technologies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/web-science', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5294960.mp4', '2015-11-30', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/91/42/regular_914240b3-f131-47cb-90a5-be0a430aa70e.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:03:17'),
(238, 'Monitoring Climate from Space', 'Explore our planet from space and learn how Earth observation is used to monitor climate change, with this free online course.', 'It is increasingly essential for us to study climate change across the planet at the highest level of detail possible. But how can we achieve such a comprehensive worldwide view?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-from-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5573782.mp4', '2015-11-30', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/e7/regular_a4e7190e-bd62-49db-a067-c447a53b8709.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'European Space Agency', '2015-11-04 00:03:18'),
(239, 'In the Night Sky: Orion', 'Explore the night sky, discover how stars formed and find out about exoplanets, all through the constellation of Orion.', 'From the basics of astronomy and stargazing, to the science behind the birth of a star, this four week course will change the way you see the night sky. Youâll examine one of the most famous constellations, Orion, who the Ancient Greeks believed was a huntsman placed among the stars by Zeus himself.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/orion', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5334054.mp4', '2016-01-04', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ae/f3/regular_aef30283-74eb-43e5-aac8-b25365494c62.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:19'),
(240, 'Cancer in the 21st Century: the Genomic Revolution', 'Discover how genetics is revolutionising the detection and treatment of cancer, with this free online course.', 'Cancer Research UK estimates that 1 in 2 people in the UK will be diagnosed with cancer during their lifetime. It is a disease that impacts on most peopleâs lives at some stage. So understanding cancer, and the development of new treatments, is of intrinsic interest to us all.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cancer-and-the-genomic-revolution', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2958909.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/6f/regular_906f023f-dbe3-40ee-a8f5-2feb04c56828.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:03:20'),
(241, 'Supply Chain Innovation: How Technology Can Create a Sustainable Future', 'Understand how new technologies can make supply chains more sustainable and learn how to deal with todays trends.', 'Every product that we use today is the result of a supply chain - a complex series of steps that turn raw materials into the final products we use and everything related with this. Managing these supply chains has become more and more a challenge, especially with all modern technologies and todays trends. The 24-hour economy, fast delivery of goods to your home, wanting to have customized products and of course the focus on sustainability are a few of these trends.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/supply-chain-innovation', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5282692.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c3/5f/regular_c35fa072-a305-4a64-8787-1529c1e13589.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Twente', '2015-11-04 00:03:20'),
(242, 'The Science of Nutrition', 'Explore the science behind what you eat with this free online course.', 'Are we really what we eat? And how do we know what is in our food?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nutrition', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4686390.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/98/c1/regular_98c184c3-0cff-44b6-87dd-fe341fc2a65a.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:21'),
(243, 'Smart Cities', 'Explore the role of technology and data in cities, and learn how you can participate in the creation of smart cities.', 'Cities are incubators of innovation and opportunities but they also face great challenges such as rapid urbanisation, climate change and inequality. How can smart cities address these challenges and become more resilient? And what role will people play in the design and planning of our smart cities?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/smart-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4320132.mp4', '2016-01-18', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c8/67/regular_c8674e50-15bc-424f-85ff-055fff956043.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:22'),
(244, 'Energy: Thermodynamics in Everyday Life', 'Understand the laws of thermodynamics â and how they govern how we use and lose energy everyday â in this free online course.', 'Energy is essential to life at many levels and its transformation from one form to another â whether in the cells of our bodies or the machines that enable modern society â is governed by the laws of thermodynamics.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5569610.mp4', '2016-02-01', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/62/regular_7162e433-558b-47e2-b263-195f8be0f45b.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'no', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:03:22'),
(245, 'Gravity! From the Big Bang to Black Holes', 'Gravity runs the Universe. This free online course explains why, focussing on key concepts from the Big Bang to black holes.', 'What is gravity? This fundamental force is the common theme between concepts as intriguing as the Big Bang, black holes, dark energy, space-time, gravitational waves and the expansion of the Universe.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/gravity', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4654030.mp4', '2015-10-26', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/57/ea/regular_57ea9287-4b25-4f25-a151-611222cce8ec.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Paris Diderot', '2015-11-04 00:03:23'),
(246, 'Identifying Food Fraud', 'An introduction to modern analytical science techniques and how they can be used to uncover food fraud.', 'The food industry is one of the most important commercial sectors in the world. Everyone uses it, but how many people abuse it? As we witness the increasing globalisation of the supply chain, a growing challenge is verifying the questionable identity of raw materials in the food we eat.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-fraud', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4991864.mp4', '2015-10-26', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/be/4e/regular_be4e9062-2ba7-4c63-82b9-d542370dccf0.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:24'),
(247, 'Numeracy Skills for Employability and the Workplace', 'Improve your mathematical confidence and gain the skills to pass employersâ numeracy tests with this free online course.', 'In our highly technical world numeracy skills, particularly the ability to interpret data, are becoming increasingly important and are highly sought after by employers.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/numeracy-skills', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3100937.mp4', '2015-10-19', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/ee/regular_efeeb9bf-a129-455c-a1f0-f4727d81bf2b.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Loughborough University', '2015-11-04 00:03:24'),
(248, 'Moons', 'Explore the many moons of our Solar System. Find out what makes them special. Should we send humans to our Moon again?', 'There are lots of moons in our Solar System. The Earth is the only planet with just a single moon. Some moons are bigger than ours; many are much smaller. There are even tiny moons orbiting some of the asteroids. Some have ongoing volcanic eruptions; others are dead, heavily cratered lumps. One has rivers and lakes of liquid methane. Our own Moon has resources that could help open the Solar System for future exploration. A small handful of moons have conditions below their surfaces where primitive life might exist.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/moons', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2096693.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/58/regular_45589460-fec1-4b42-96d9-ecd89c0a4e13.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:25'),
(249, 'Data to Insight: An Introduction to Data Analysis', 'This course is a hands-on introduction to statistical data analysis that emphasises fundamental concepts and practical skills.', 'Organisations around the world are collecting more data than ever. They are talking about big data, data science, business intelligence, analytics, data mining and data visualisation, and thereâs an urgent need for people with the data skills to understand, interpret and communicate this information.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/data-to-insight', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1644667.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e5/09/regular_e50950a6-e653-4933-9443-6a25900440be.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Auckland', '2015-11-04 00:03:25'),
(250, 'Maths for Humans: Linear, Quadratic & Inverse Relations', 'Strengthen your algebra, geometry and thinking skills by learning about the maths behind real-world relations.', 'Whatâs the connection between the size of a city and the number of gas stations in it? How would you describe this relationship? How would you try to visualise and understand it?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/maths-linear-quadratic', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5061728.mp4', '2015-10-12', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c7/29/regular_c7294421-21da-4753-a06e-cb9abb3714d8.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:03:26'),
(251, 'Ultrasound Imaging: What Is Inside?', 'Understand the technology of ultrasound, see how it is used in clinical practice and learn how to improve medical imaging.', 'Ultrasound is an easy and quick technique to visualize structures inside the human body. It is a relatively harmless and accessible technique. It has been used for decades in medical practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ultrasound-imaging', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4508377.mp4', '2015-10-05', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e1/39/regular_e1390375-f5b0-4893-9edf-3d36671ec508.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Twente', '2015-11-04 00:03:27'),
(252, 'Smart Cities', 'Explore the role of technology and data in cities, and learn how you can participate in the creation of smart cities.', 'Cities are incubators of innovation and opportunities but they also face great challenges such as rapid urbanisation, climate change and inequality. How can smart cities address these challenges and become more resilient? And what role will people play in the design and planning of our smart cities?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/smart-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4320132.mp4', '2015-09-28', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fe/2e/regular_fe2ebb01-4e0a-44ec-bbc9-490420a8017f.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:27'),
(253, 'Assessment for Learning in STEM Teaching', 'A free online course led by Dylan Wiliam and Christine Harrison, to help STEM teachers get to grips with Assessment for Learning.', 'Assessment for Learning is a term thatâs widely used in education, but applied in ways that are variable in their effectiveness. This free online course - designed for STEM teachers in primary and secondary schools, and sixth form and further education (FE) colleges - will help you understand and use it more effectively.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/assessment-for-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428566.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/49/67/regular_49671185-1361-47f7-b320-5e36fe2a2883.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:28'),
(254, 'Basic Science: Understanding Experiments', 'This hands-on course introduces you to science-based skills through simple and exciting physics, chemistry and biology experiments', 'This practical, hands-on course aims to help you start thinking like a scientist by carrying out experiments at home and making scientific observations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/science-experiments', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1631019.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/35/c4/regular_35c4e997-3fb2-4a60-b9ea-6c7d8741d04d.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:28'),
(255, 'Begin Robotics', 'Explore the history, anatomy and intelligence of robots with this free online course. Test drive robots using exciting simulations', 'Robots today are roving Mars, collecting data in dangerous environments, hoovering our floors, lifting patients in hospital, building cars and entertaining us in films. And, if you share Bill Gates and Stephen Hawkingâs world view, the super intelligent ones may one day bring about the end of the human race.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-robotics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3697356.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/ce/regular_82ce6165-30a4-440e-ad57-a7e8f9e77220.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:03:29'),
(256, 'Causes of Climate Change', 'Understand the physical processes behind climate variations in the past, present and future, with this free online course', 'This free online course provides the basis for understanding the underlying physical processes governing climate variations in the past, present and future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-climate-change', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4147256.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a1/84/regular_a184ac4b-f773-4ba7-87bb-fb9a23b1792c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bergen', '2015-11-04 00:03:30'),
(257, 'Climate Change: Challenges and Solutions', 'This course aims to explain the science of climate change, the risks it poses and the solutions available to reduce those risks.', 'The course is aimed at the level of students entering university, and seeks to provide an inter-disciplinary introduction to what is a broad field. It engages a number of experts from the University of Exeter and a number of partner organisations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-change-challenges-and-solutions', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2136990.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/cb/71/regular_cb71114d-b163-4486-908d-20dadfde623e.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Exeter', '2015-11-04 00:03:30'),
(258, 'Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World', 'This course will teach you the first principles of complexity, uncertainty and how to make decisions in a complex world.', 'Leaders must be able to act in a complex world and under uncertainty. This course is a first step to develop yourself into one of the futureâs key decision makers or to enhance your decision-making skills.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/complexity-and-uncertainty', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2182037.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f6/28/regular_f6280438-ac86-4f67-9ff2-6d5bdda3e9ea.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:03:31'),
(259, 'Discover Dentistry', 'An entertaining and illuminating course for everyone to explore the impact dentistry has on our lives.', 'How important is a smile? Ever wondered what all those letters and numbers a dentist calls out during your check-up mean? How are broken teeth fixed, or how dentures are made? Join Dr Christopher Stokes on a learning journey to explore the dental profession and the impact dentistry has on all our lives.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/discover-dentistry', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3951348.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c9/0a/regular_c90a27ee-232d-4bd6-bc98-aa66ec60d481.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:03:31'),
(260, 'Dysphagia: Swallowing Difficulties and Medicines', 'This course will enhance the knowledge of any person involved in the administration of medicines to patients with dysphagia.', 'The course offers an opportunity to network with other learners and with the creators of the course through discussions, graphs and social networking features and to share knowledge with other learners and professionals. By completing this online course participants will be able to describe:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dysphagia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3261218.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/16/6c/regular_166c19c9-7eab-48da-b7b8-c21e383c1f58.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:32'),
(261, 'Ebola in Context: Understanding Transmission, Response and Control', 'How has the Ebola outbreak become a humanitarian emergency? Learn about the science behind the crisis.', 'In 2014, Ebola went from a scarcely known virus to the subject of daily news reports. The epidemic in West Africa has quickly surpassed all previous outbreaks, to become an unprecedented humanitarian crisis.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ebola-in-context', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2714612.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/1b/regular_461b7c93-fba6-4151-a140-cbdf9422c2bf.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine', '2015-11-04 00:03:32'),
(262, 'Ebola: Symptoms, History and Origins', 'Learn about Ebola, its symptoms, where it came from and what the current outbreak has taught us, with this free online course.', 'In December 2013, the largest outbreak of Ebola virus disease (EVD) that the world has ever seen, began in West Africa - a region of the continent that has historically been free of it.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ebola', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3089045.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/5e/regular_d95ef0b5-c747-4815-bcde-26ebc3d0f87d.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:03:33'),
(263, 'Elements of Renewable Energy', 'Learn how sustainable energy from the Greek elements â Earth, Air, Fire and Water â can replace fossil fuels and nuclear power.', 'In recent decades thereâs been increasing global concern about the sustainability of our use of fossil fuels and nuclear power, which has led to increased interest in more sustainable renewable energy sources.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/elements-renewable-energies', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0e/e1/regular_0ee1deec-38ac-46df-82a5-4d4b0f0bad4c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:34'),
(264, 'Exploring Anatomy: the Human Abdomen', 'Explore the anatomy of the human abdomen and understand its clinical importance.', 'This course introduces you to the human abdomen and explores its many complex structures. As the course progresses, the structure and function of important organs will be demonstrated, discussed and related to common surgical scenarios and current research. Each of the three weeks will focus on a specific area of the abdomen; starting at the surface you will then enter the abdomen and be able to detail the anatomy of numerous organs including the stomach and liver.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/anatomy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2321495.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0c/d4/regular_0cd42bec-6ea7-425f-9306-c84c455c8c6f.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:35');
