(3119, 'Climate Change: The Science', 'Do you want to talk about climate change from an informed perspective?', 'Do you want to talk about climate change from an informed perspective? Are you interested in how global warming works? Climate change is the biggest challenge of our time, and climate science is critical to finding solutions. How can we make the best decisions about our present and future? By taking this course, you can be part of the global conversation.Â  Climate Change: The Science is an introduction to climate science basics. Weâll discuss flows of energy and carbon in Earthâs climate system, how climate models work, climate history, and future forecasts. This course will give you the knowledge you need, and practice communicating about climate change. Youâll meet people from around the world with a huge range of local and regional climate change issues. Join us, learn the science, and share your own stories. ', 'https://edx.org/course/climate-change-science-ubcx-climate1x', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/r9mopioqk-8?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-10-14', 49, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/climate1x_banner.jpg?itok=CwCZStiP', 'Science', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'UBCx', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
