(3233, 'Entrepreneurship and Healthcare in Emerging Economies', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning.', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning. All features and materials may not be all available. Check back often to see when new course start dates are announced.  Entrepreneurship and Healthcare in Emerging Economies aims to engage students in an inter-disciplinary approach to understanding the nature of complex health problems throughout the world, with an illustrative focus on South Asia. Students will become acquainted with prior attempts to address these problems, to identify points of opportunity for smart entrepreneurial efforts, and to propose and develop their own candidate solutions. Throughout, the emphasis is on individual agencyâwhat can the learner do to address a defined problem? While we use the lens of health to explore entrepreneurial opportunities, students will see that both problems and solutions are inevitably of a multi-disciplinary nature, and we will draw on a range of sectors and fields of study. HarvardX pursues the science of learning. By registering as an online learner in an HX course, you will also participate in research about learning. Read our research statement to learn more. ', 'https://edx.org/course/entrepreneurship-healthcare-emerging-harvardx-sw47-1x', '', '2015-11-24', 84, '', 'Business & Management', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'no', 'HarvardX', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3234, 'Epidemics', 'âIf history is our guide, we can assume that the battle between the intellect and will of the human species and the extraordinary adaptability of microbes will be never-ending.', 'âIf history is our guide, we can assume that the battle between the intellect and will of the human species and the extraordinary adaptability of microbes will be never-ending.â (1) Despite all the remarkable technological breakthroughs that we have made over the past few decades, the threat from infectious diseases has significantly accelerated. In this course, we will learn why this is the case by looking at the fundamental scientific principles underlying epidemics and the public health actions behind their prevention and control in the 21st century. This course covers these four topics: (1) Fauci AS, Touchette NA, Folkers GK. Emerging Infectious Diseases: a 10-Year Perspective from the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases. Emerg Infect Dis 2005 Apr; 11(4):519-25. ', 'https://edx.org/course/epidemics-hkux-hku01x-0', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/C0_6tr_O1MI?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-09-15', 70, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/hku01x-course_image-378x225a.png?itok=8RleNvwj', 'Health & Safety', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'no', 'HKUx', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3235, 'Essential Human Biology: Cells and Tissues', 'Are you preparing for a health-related career, or planning to study in the health sciences?', 'Are you preparing for a health-related career, or planning to study in the health sciences? Perhaps you''re just keen to learn more about the wonders of the human body? Our bodies are amazing but complex biological machines. This course will provide you with an outstanding foundation of knowledge in human anatomy and physiology. Â  You will gain a broad understanding of the relationships between normal structure and function in human cells and tissues, both in health and disease. The properties of the four main types of tissue in the body - epithelial, connective, muscular and nervous - will also be clearly explained. Â  The course employs a variety of engaging learning methods, including short videos, animations, interactive activities and integrated quizzes to guide you through key concepts, and make learning relevant.Â  Â  ', 'https://edx.org/course/essential-human-biology-cells-tissues-adelaidex-humbio101x-0', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/7tCOJ61Jxeo?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 35, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/essential-human-biology-cells-and-tissues_378x225.jpg?itok=AqsFZbq7', 'Biology & Life Sciences', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'AdelaideX', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3236, 'Essentials of Nonprofit Strategy', 'A nonprofit''s strategy determines whether the organization will sink or swim.', 'A nonprofit''s strategy determines whether the organization will sink or swim. Nonetheless, nonprofit leaders are often unable or unwilling to plan in the short-term to achieve long-lasting social change. This course will help you develop successful strategies to achieve your organization''s goals and make strides towards meaningful impact. Using the social problems of homelessness and childhood obesity as real world examples, you will learn how to undertake the basic elements of strategy: defining the problem, identifying stakeholders, designing a theory of change and logic model, and establishing assessment criteria. With this foundation, you will be able to develop strategies that will ensure long-term impact for your own organizationsârather than just the illusion of results.', 'https://novoed.com/philanthropy-university-strategy', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/q4W7KAfpph0?vq=auto&rel=0&showinfo=0&autohide=1&wmode=transparent&origin=https://novoed.com', '2015-09-29', 50, '', '', 'NovoEd', -1, 'English', 'no', 'Philanthropy University', '2015-11-24 23:09:29'),
(3237, 'Estrategia: En vez de competir, innove', 'Una estrategia es un conjunto de decisiones complementarias orientadas a crear y mantener buenos negocios.', 'Una estrategia es un conjunto de decisiones complementarias orientadas a crear y mantener buenos negocios. Para ganar mÃ¡s hay que competir menos. Solo la constante renovaciÃ³n de la estrategia permite ganar sin competir legÃ­timamente. Las empresas deben innovar para descubrir nuevas oportunidades de negocios que permitan proyectar un crecimiento rentable. Esto en un contexto donde los buenos negocios son cada vez mÃ¡s difÃ­ciles de encontrar y cada vez menos duraderos. Este curso explica en un leguaje accesible a todos cÃ³mo aplicar los principales conceptos vigentes de estrategia en la formulaciÃ³n de un plan de negocios creativo. Estos conceptos incluyen: contexto competitivo y cooperativo, red de valor, co-opeticiÃ³n, ventaja competitiva por costo y en diferenciaciÃ³n, valor agregado, sustentaciÃ³n, amenazas de imitaciÃ³n y sustituciÃ³n, amenazas de retenciÃ³n e ineficiencia, recursos y capacidades, coherencia interna y externa, creatividad e innovaciÃ³n estratÃ©gica, compromisos irreversibles, decisiones estratÃ©gicas, flexibilidad e incertidumbre, patching, crecimiento rÃ­tmico, y reglas simples. Este curso gratuito de cinco semanas estÃ¡ orientado a todos los que hablan espaÃ±ol que desean mejorar sus competencias en la formulaciÃ³n de estrategias de negocios, y establecer simultÃ¡neamente redes con hispano parlantes alrededor de todo el mundo. El curso incluye videos y lecturas, y hace amplio uso de casos para introducir las materias en forma realista y estimulante. Los estudiantes desarrollarÃ¡ un proyecto trabajando en equipo a distancia y habrÃ¡ retroalimentaciÃ³n entre los diferentes grupos. Ph.D. Stanford University', 'https://novoed.com/Estrategia', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/jH_y3m10sjk?vq=auto&rel=0&showinfo=0&autohide=1&wmode=transparent&origin=https://novoed.com', '2014-10-02', 57, '', 