(3353, 'IntroducciÃ³n al Control NumÃ©rico por Computadora | Introduction to Computer Numerical Control', 'Con este curso aprenderÃ¡s a desarrollar y operar un proyecto con una mÃ¡quina CNC, a travÃ©s de la simulaciÃ³n de un caso real y con el objetivo de producir piezas de ajedrez para una empresa llamada âJaque Mateâ.', 'Con este curso aprenderÃ¡s a desarrollar y operar un proyecto con una mÃ¡quina CNC, a travÃ©s de la simulaciÃ³n de un caso real y con el objetivo de producir piezas de ajedrez para una empresa llamada âJaque Mateâ. De esta forma, irÃ¡s adquiriendo los conocimientos necesarios para tomar decisiones en cada etapa del proyecto (desde la interpretaciÃ³n de un plano hasta el mecanizado y control de calidad de las piezas) y asÃ­ cumplir con el pedido del cliente. Para resolver los desafÃ­os que se proponen en cada secciÃ³n, el curso cuenta con una serie de videos teÃ³ricos e interactivos que facilitan el aprendizaje del uso y control de una mÃ¡quina CNC. ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduccion-al-control-numerico-por-tenarisuniversity-cnc-etrrx3', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/s9QLn9Pj5dE?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 28, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/cnc.etrrx_3-course_image-378x225.png?itok=29YwDiXf', 'Engineering', 'edX', 0, 'EspaÃ±ol', 'no', 'TenarisUniversity', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3354, 'Introduction to Actuarial Science', 'Actuary is rated the best job of 2015 by CareerCast.', 'Actuary is rated the best job of 2015 by CareerCast.com because it pays well and offers abundant opportunities for advancement.Â  You may have heard of actuarial science, or you might even know an actuary, but do you know what an actuary does? During the course youâll hear from a wide variety of actuaries about their careers. And donât be scared that the course will be âjust a whole lot of mathematicsâ. Together, we will go beyond the math to learn how actuaries approach problems relating to risk, using examples from: You will learn how actuarial science applies mathematical and statistical methods to assess risk in these industries and other professions. Youâll experience âhands-onâ learning using Excel (or an equivalent spreadsheet tool) to project and investigate the financial condition of a company choosing appropriate strategies for the company through the use of simulations. The course has been carefully designed for students from a wide variety of backgrounds, with secondary/high school level being the only assumption of mathematical background. Even if you donât have any background in, for example, calculus, the course has been designed so you can skip over these sections without affecting your understanding of the rest of the course. You also do not need to have any Excel or other spreadsheet background to take the course. For those with stronger mathematical backgrounds, extension questions are provided to test you further. Youâll learn a huge amount about actuarial science no matter what your background is! Join us today. To connect with the course community before and during the course, join our Facebook group, and tweet us with #actuarialedX. ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-actuarial-science-anux-anu-actuarialx', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/xnRVSXUmeAE?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-10-16', 56, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/actuarialx-about_page_image-318x210.png?itok=dH7N2--L', 'Economics & Finance', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'ANUx', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3355, 'Introduction to Aerodynamics', 'This aerodynamics course focuses on the study of the flow of air about a body, and the âbodyâ will be an airplane, but many of the concepts explored are relevant to a wide variety of applications from sailboats to automobiles to birds.', 'This aerodynamics course focuses on the study of the flow of air about a body, and the âbodyâ will be an airplane, but many of the concepts explored are relevant to a wide variety of applications from sailboats to automobiles to birds. Learners completing this aerodynamics course will gain a fundamental understanding of concepts and models used to aerodynamically analyze and design subsonic, transonic, and supersonic aircraft. While the course is an introduction to aerodynamics, it is an advanced subject typically taken as a third or fourth year undergraduate subject in aerospace engineering. ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-aerodynamics-mitx-16-101x-0', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/bIC1JNgwaK8?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-09-28', 119, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/16101x_378x225_0.jpg?itok=wDlwktqB', 'Engineering', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'MITx', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3356, 'Introduction to Aeronautical Engineering', 'This course provides an overview of and introduction to the fundamentals of aeronautics, using the history of aviation as a story line.', 'This course provides an overview of and introduction to the fundamentals of aeronautics, using the history of aviation as a story line. The course uses examples from the very beginning of aviation (the Montgolfier brothersâ balloon flight in 1783 and the Wright brothersâ heavier-than-air flight in 1903) and continues all the way through to the current Airbus A380 and future aircraft. During this trajectory three major topics are discussed: aeronautics, aerodynamics and flight mechanics. Lectures are frequently accompanied by related exercises and demonstrations. The course also incorporates (design) challenges/competitions, based on the knowledge obtained through the lectures. FAQ Roughly how many hours will I have to spend on the course? We estimate it will take 84 hours to complete this course. As this course is self-paced, you can choose when you work on it. How much does it cost to take the course? Nothing! The course is free. Will the text of the lectures be available? Yes. All of our lectures will have transcripts synced to the videos. Do I need to watch the lectures live? No. You can watch the lectures at your leisure. Will certificates be awarded? Yes. Online learners who achieve a passing grade in a course are awarded a certificate of mastery. The certificate indicates that the learner has successfully completed the course, but does not include a specific grade. Certificates are issued by edX under the name of DelftX, designating the institution from which the course originated. Can I contact the instructor or teaching assistants? Yes, but not directly. The discussion forums are the appropriate venue for questions about the course. The instructors monitor the discussion forums and try to respond to the most important questions; in many cases response from other students and peers will be both adequate and faster. Is this course related to a TU Delft campus course? The material treated in this course forms part of the BSc programme in Aerospace Engineering, but the MOOC certificate does not offer any exemptions. LICENSE The course materials of this course are Copyright Delft University of Technology and are licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike (CC-BY-NC-SA) 4.0 International License. ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-aeronautical-engineering-delftx-ae1110x-0', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/jaMWrQXh2PQ?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', -1, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/ae1110x_aeronautical_course_featured380x168.jpg?itok=K9VSOW-L', 'Engineering', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'no', 'DelftX', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3357, 'Introduction to Aerospace Engineering: Astronautics and Human Spaceflight', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning.', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning. All features and materials may not be all available. Check back often to see when new course start dates are announced.  Spaceflight is exciting, and you donât have to be a âRocket Scientistâ to share in the excitement! 16.00x makes the basics of spaceflight accessible to everyone. Join MIT Professor Jeffrey Hoffman, a former NASA astronaut who made five spaceflights and was the first astronaut to log 1000 hours on the Space Shuttle, as he teaches you the core principles behind space travel and exploration.Â  The course will cover how rockets work, how spacecraft move in orbit, how we create artificial environments inside spacecraft to keep astronauts alive and healthy, what itâs like living in a world without gravity, how the human body adapts to space, and how spacewalks happen, plus more. Many lessons will be illustrated with Professor Hoffmanâs own experiences in space.Â  ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-aerospace-engineering-mitx-16-00x', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/Nugc_RO56cQ?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 56, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/intro-to-aerospace_378x225.jpg?itok=U9Tl3iiA', 'Engineering', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'MITx', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3358, 'Introduction to Algebra', 'We live in a world of numbers.', 'We live in a world of numbers. You see them every day: on clocks, in the stock market, in sports, and all over the news. Algebra is all about figuring out the numbers youÂ don''tÂ see. You might know how fast you can throw a ball, but can you use this number to determine howÂ farÂ you can throw it? You might keep track of stock prices, but how can you figure out how much money you''ve made (or lost) in the market? And you may already know how to tell time, but can you calculate at what times a clock''s hour and minute hands areÂ exactlyÂ aligned? With algebra, you can answer all of these questions, using the numbers you already know to solve for theÂ unknown. Algebra is an essential tool for all of high school and college-level math, science, and engineering. So if you''re starting out in one of these fields and you haven''t yet mastered algebra, then this is the course for you! Â  In this course, you''ll be able to choose your own path within each lesson, and you can jump between lessons to quickly review earlier material. AlgebraX covers a standard curriculum in high school Algebra I, and CCSS (common core) alignment is indicated where applicable. Learn more about our High School and AP* Exam Preparation Courses ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-algebra-schoolyourself-algebrax', '', '2015-11-24', -1, '', 'Math', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'SchoolYourself', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3359, 'Introduction to Big Data with Apache Spark', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning.', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning. All features and materials may not be all available. Check back often to see when new course start dates are announced.  Organizations use their data for decision support and to build data-intensive products and services, such as recommendation, prediction, and diagnostic systems. The collection of skills required by organizations to support these functions has been grouped under the term Data Science. This course will attempt to articulate the expected output of Data Scientists and then teach students how to use PySpark (part of Apache Spark) to deliver against these expectations. The course assignments include Log Mining, Textual Entity Recognition, Collaborative Filtering exercises that teach students how to manipulate data sets using parallel processing with PySpark. This course covers advanced undergraduate-level material. It requires a programming background and experience with Python (or the ability to learn it quickly). All exercises will use PySpark (part of Apache Spark), but previous experience with Spark or distributed computing is NOT required. Students should take this Python mini-quiz before the course and take this Python mini-course if they need to learn Python or refresh their Python knowledge. Â  ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-big-data-apache-spark-uc-berkeleyx-cs100-1x', '', '2015-11-24', 35, '', 'Computer Science', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'UC BerkeleyX', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3360, 'Introduction to Bioelectricity', 'In this course you will use fundamental engineering and mathematical tools to understand and analyze basic bioelectricity and circuit theory in the context of the mammalian nervous system.', 'In this course you will use fundamental engineering and mathematical tools to understand and analyze basic bioelectricity and circuit theory in the context of the mammalian nervous system. Â  This course is for students who are interested in learning about relating the systems of the human body that involve or communicate with bioelectrical systems, including the heart, brain, muscles, and the neuromuscular system that connects them all together.Â  Students will learn how bioelectricity can be used to record and control the way the body electric behaves. Suggested text: âNeuroscienceâ by Purves, et al.Â  This course is offered by the nanoHUB-U project , which is jointly funded by Purdue and NSF with the goal of transcending disciplines through short courses accessible to students in any branch of science or engineering. These courses focus on cutting-edge topics distilled into short lectures with quizzes, homework, and practice exams. ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-bioelectricity-purduex-nano525x', '', '2015-11-24', 112, '', 'Engineering', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'PurdueX', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
(3361, 'Introduction to Bioethics', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning.', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning. All features and materials may not be all available. Check back often to see when new course start dates are announced.  Should we clone humans? What should we think of the coming genetic revolution? How much control should we have over how and when we die? When does medical treatment turn into medical enhancement â and should we care? Is rationing health care good, bad, necessary â or all of the above? This course will explore fundamental moral issues that arise in medicine, health, and biotechnology. Get behind the headlines â and polarized debates â and join others who want to think deeply and openly about these problems. Some are as old as life itself: the vulnerability of illness, the fact of death. Some are new, brought on by a dizzying pace of technology that can unsettle our core ideas about human nature and our place in the world. And nearly all intersect with issues of racial and gender equality, as well as policies affecting the worldâs most vulnerable populations. Designed to introduce students to the range of issues that define bioethics, together with core concepts and skills, this course should be of interest to undergraduates, health care professionals, policy makers, and anyone interested in philosophy or ethics. Before your course starts, try the new edX Demo where you can explore the fun, interactive learning environment and virtual labs.Â Learn more. ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-bioethics-georgetownx-phlx101-02x', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/62_EDCyeuxs?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 70, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/bioethics_378x225.jpg?itok=EfbBsKuX', 'Biology & Life Sciences', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'no', 'GeorgetownX', '2015-11-24 23:09:31');
