(3409, 'Introduction to R Programming', 'R is rapidly becoming the leading language in data science and statistics.', 'R is rapidly becoming the leading language in data science and statistics. Today, the R programming language is the tool of choice for data scientists in every industry and field. Whether you are a full-time number cruncher, or just the occasional data analyst, R will suit your needs.Â  This introduction to R programming course will help you master the basics of R. In sevenÂ sections, youÂ will cover its basic syntax, making you ready to undertake your own first data analysis using R. Starting from variables and basic operations, you willÂ learn how to handle data structures such as vectors, matrices, data frames and lists. In the finalÂ section, youÂ will dive deeper into the graphical capabilities of R, and create your own stunning data visualizations.Â No prior knowledge in programming or data science is required. Â  What makes this R programming course unique is that you will continuously practice your newly acquired skills through interactive in-browser coding challenges using the DataCamp platform. InsteadÂ of passively watching videos, you will solve real data problems while receiving instant and personalized feedback that guides you to the correct solution. Â  Enjoy!Â  ', 'https://edx.org/course/introduction-r-programming-microsoft-dat204x-0', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/2kC46yj4Heg?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 28, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/dat204x-course_image-378x225.png?itok=zZwa7R-m', 'Data Analysis & Statistics', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Microsoft', '2015-11-24 23:09:31'),
