(4720, 'Reason and Persuasion: Thinking Through Three Dialogues By Plato', 'In this course we will study Platos ancient art of blowing up your beliefs as you go, to make sure theyre built to last. We spend six weeks studying three Platonic dialogues, then two more weeks pondering a pair of footnotes to Plato; that is, we will consider some contemporary manifestations of issues Plato discusses. Our focus will be: moral theory and moral psychology. ', 'In this course we will study Platos ancient art of blowing up your beliefs as you go, to make sure theyre built to last. We spend six weeks studying three Platonic dialogues, then two more weeks pondering a pair of footnotes to Plato; that is, we will consider some contemporary manifestations of issues Plato discusses. Our focus will be: moral theory and moral psychology. ', 'https://class.coursera.org/reasonandpersuasion-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=43b8acd076fc11e4bd3a5d0390e46cec', '2015-01-12', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/2e/abd27b5ded8b660d20c3ae79c1a4d5/courselogo.jpg', 'Social Sciences,Arts,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'National University of Singapore,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
